# Project organization

**Phase focus:** control-plane foundations + capabilities (`F*` / `C*`). Prefer extending existing packages over new top-level folders. Domain authority lives in `domain` / `application`; Temporal, Docker, Redis fan-out, and Agents SDK are mechanics, not truth. Vocabulary/specs: prefer `biotech-meta` over inventing names.

## Layout

| Path | Role |
|------|------|
| `app/domain/` | Pure contracts / invariants (no I/O). Current packages: `control_plane`, `run_control`, `composition`, `orchestration`, `operation_execution` |
| `app/application/` | Use-cases, ports, Postgres/Mongo adapters for control plane |
| `app/api/` | FastAPI surfaces (`control_plane`, `run_control`) |
| `app/models/` | Persistence-facing Beanie/docs shapes |
| `app/integrations/` | Vendor adapters (Mongo, Postgres, Neo4j, S3, Temporal, Agents SDK, realtime) |
| `app/temporal/` | Workflows, activities, workers, probes |
| `app/migrations/` | Application Postgres schema migrations |
| `app/middleware/` | ASGI/HTTP middleware |
| `tests/` | Unit + integration tests |
| `infra/` | Compose-adjacent init/scripts (not domain) |
| `docs/` | Local diagrams / operator notes — not product authority |
| `sandbox-work/` | Disposable experiments — not product authority |
| `scripts/` | Operator/dev scripts |
| `.scratch/` | Working issues, handoffs, lifecycle — NOT durable product docs |
| `.scratch/control-plane-foundations-and-capabilities/issues/` | Active control-plane ticket mirrors |
| `../biotech-meta/docs/specs/` | Accepted specifications |
| `../biotech-meta/docs/checkpoints/` | Interview/architecture checkpoints |

## Hard rules

- Do not treat `.scratch/`, `sandbox-work/`, or `docs/` as production contracts.
- Put business truth in `app/domain/` and `app/application/`; keep I/O and vendors in `integrations` / `temporal` / `api`.
- When naming or deciding scope, check `biotech-meta` specs/checkpoints before inventing terms or new top-level structure.
- Do not invent Workflow Type or dashboard behavior ahead of accepted tickets; build seams the later types will consume.
